{"title":"Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #24: Ribble Allroad SL R","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-ribble-allroad-sl-r","date":1743174575000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-ribble-allroad-sl-r\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #24: Ribble Allroad SL R</a></p>\n\n<p>Whether you’re on the lookout for a new bike or just want to try out some of the world’s best, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> offer a unique experience to test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next up in our rundown of some of the incredible bikes that you can test ride at this years Track Days is the Ribble Allroad SL R.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Allroad SL R is Ribble’s all-new all-road bike, meaning it’s a road bike that’s built for comfort and light off-road capability. However this isn’t your standard <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-all-road-bikes\">all-road bike</a>, when Cyclist deputy editor James Spender reviewed it at the end of last year, he described it as ‘an aero bike for normal riders, with a stiff frame tempered by wide tyres’. The model he rode was built with a Shimano Dura-Ace Di2 groupset with Zipp 353 NSW wheels. That weighed in at 8.1kg and is priced at £8,299.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read James’s full review <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/ribble-allroad-sl-r-road-bike-review\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ribble Allroad SL R will be at the following Track Days events:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>26<sup>th</sup> April 2025, Odd Down Cycle Track Bath,<br />17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London,<br />7<sup>th</sup> June 2025, The Brownlee Centre, Leeds</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n 